```
You are extending Inkframe, an AI-powered animated video/interactive 
explainer creator. The app already has:
- 5 scene types: svg, motion, d3, three, lottie
- WebVideoCreator + FFmpeg export pipeline (MP4)
- Zustand state, Next.js frontend, Express render server
- Scene HTML files written to /public/scenes/{id}.html

## GOAL
Add a dual output mode system:

  MODE 1 — "Export MP4"     (existing pipeline, unchanged)
  MODE 2 — "Publish Interactive" (new: hosted iframe with live interactivity)

The user picks the mode per-project. Same scenes, same editor, 
two completely different outputs. Interactive mode keeps everything 
as live HTML/JS — no video encoding at all.

