## PART 3 — INTERACTIVE PLAYER RUNTIME

### 3.1 Player Package

Create a separate package: /packages/player/

This is a self-contained JS runtime that can be embedded anywhere.
It should be buildable as a single JS file via Vite:

  /packages/player/
  ├── src/
  │   ├── index.ts           # entry point, exports InkframePlayer class
  │   ├── runtime.ts         # scene sequencer + state machine
  │   ├── renderer.ts        # iframe management
  │   ├── interactions.ts    # interaction element rendering + event handling
  │   ├── variables.ts       # variable store
  │   └── ui/
  │       ├── controls.ts    # play/pause/progress bar
  │       ├── hotspot.ts     # hotspot element renderer
  │       ├── choice.ts      # choice button renderer
  │       ├── quiz.ts        # quiz renderer
  │       ├── gate.ts        # gate/continue button renderer
  │       ├── tooltip.ts     # tooltip renderer
  │       └── form.ts        # form renderer
  ├── package.json
  └── vite.config.ts         # builds to single inkframe-player.min.js

Player API:

```ts
class InkframePlayer {
