## PART 4 — PUBLISH PIPELINE

### 4.1 Publish API Route

POST /api/publish
Body: { projectId: string }

Server logic:
1. Collect all scene HTML files from /public/scenes/
2. Collect all uploaded assets from /public/uploads/
3. Generate the PublishedProject JSON manifest
4. Write everything to /public/published/{projectId}/
   ├── manifest.json
   ├── scenes/
   │   ├── {sceneId}.html
   │   └── ...
   └── assets/
       └── (uploaded videos, audio, lottie files)
5. Return { publishedUrl: 'https://inkframe.io/v/{projectId}' }

### 4.2 Published Project Viewer Route

Next.js route: /v/[projectId]/page.tsx

This page:
- Fetches /published/{projectId}/manifest.json
- Renders a full-screen div with the Inkframe Player
- No editor chrome — just the player
- Handles password protection if set
- Has og:image meta tag (first scene thumbnail)
- Responsive: scales player to fit viewport using CSS transform scale

```tsx
// /app/v/[projectId]/page.tsx
export default async function ViewerPage({ params }) {
  const manifest = await fetchManifest(params.projectId);
  
  return (
    <div style={{ 
      width: '100vw', height: '100vh', 
      background: '#000',
      display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center'
    }}>
      <InkframePlayerComponent
        manifest={manifest}
        autoplay={true}
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

