## PART 5 — MP4 MODE INTERACTION BAKING (optional)

When exporting MP4 from a project that has interaction elements,
offer a choice:

"Your project has interactive elements. How should they appear in the MP4?"

Option A — "Skip interactions" 
  MP4 plays through linearly, interaction elements don't appear.
  Best for a clean passive video.

Option B — "Show interactions as visuals"
  Interaction elements are "baked in" as SVG overlays added to 
  the scene HTML before WVC renders it:
  - Hotspots appear as pulsing circles
  - Choice buttons appear as visible buttons (static, not clickable)
  - Quiz shows the question (no answer interaction)
  - Gate shows the continue button (scene auto-continues after 2s)
  This creates a "preview" feel — viewer sees what's interactive 
  but in video form.

Option C — "Follow a path"
  User picks one path through the scene graph.
  Editor shows the branch points and user selects which option 
  to follow at each. WVC renders that specific linear path as MP4.
  Great for creating "demo walkthrough" videos of specific flows.

