## PART 6 — ANALYTICS (lightweight)

For published interactive projects, add basic analytics:

POST /api/analytics (called by the player runtime)
Events:
  - project_started
  - scene_viewed { sceneId, duration }
  - interaction_fired { sceneId, interactionId, type, value }
  - path_taken { fromSceneId, toSceneId, edgeCondition }
  - project_completed
  - variable_set { name, value }

Store in a simple SQLite database (use better-sqlite3, MIT licensed):
  /data/analytics.db

Analytics dashboard at /dashboard/[projectId]/analytics:
  - Total views
  - Completion rate
  - Most common paths (sankey/flow diagram via D3)
  - Drop-off scenes (where users stop)
  - Quiz correct/wrong ratios
  - Choice distribution (which options people pick)
  - Variable values collected from forms

This is a huge value-add for enterprise clients doing onboarding —
they can see exactly where new users get confused.

